descript.abstract: This dataset provides eight feature classes. The base feature class is called Country_us and isn't generalized. The weighted centroids feature class is called Country_us_cent. The centroids are weighted by the U.S. Block Centroids population distribution. Use the weighted centroids in report aggregation and spatial overlay operations. The Country_us and Country_us_cent feature classes contain all the attributes. There are six generalized boundaries feature classes and called: Country_us_gen2, Country_us_gen3, Country_us_gen4, Country_us_gen5, Country_us_gen6 and Country_us_gen7. Use the generalized boundaries when creating study areas.
descript.purpose: United States provide detailed boundaries that are consistent with the tract and county data sets and are effective at the national level.
descript.supplinf: Largest scale when displaying the data (non-generalized feature classes): 1:100,000.

citeinfo.title: United States, United States Centroids, United States (generalized)
citeinfo.othercit: U.S. Block Centroids provides geospatial data to create the weighted centroids feature class.

procstep.procdesc: The following steps were performed by Esri: For unchanged Geographies, Block Groups, Tracts, Counties, States and US: The data sets were copied from ArcGIS Business Analyst. All attributes were removed but ID, NAME, RG_NAME, RG_ABBREV, AREA, Shape, and Genshp (the generalized Shape attribute). The following Geographies: CBSA, DMA, and Zip5 boundaries, used the Jan 2015 Teleatlas release of these data sets. All geographies reprojected all the data layers to Web Mercator (Auxiliary Sphere). An in-house, custom tool was used to generate a weighted centroid shapefile of This dataset from U.S. Block Centroids. The Esri Community Data attributes were joined , which were exported out of our Data Production environment into FGDB format.

dataqual.logic: The data set is converted to FGDB (File Geodatabase) format using either Esri Geoprocessing tools in ArcGIS.
dataqual.complete: After processing, the data set is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials. This dataset provides two levels of generalization.

horizpa.horizpar: The horizontal positional accuracy is 167 feet for the base feature class <data set name>. This feature class also has the highest horizontal positional accuracy.

dataIdInfo.idPurp: United States provides detailed boundaries that are consistent with the tract and county data sets and are effective at the national level.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: This dataset provides eight feature classes. The base feature class is called Country_us and isn't generalized. The weighted centroids feature class is called Country_us_cent. The centroids are weighted by the U.S. Block Centroids population distribution. Use the weighted centroids in report aggregation and spatial overlay operations. The Country_us and Country_us_cent feature classes contain all the attributes. There are six generalized boundaries feature classes and called: Country_us_gen2, Country_us_gen3, Country_us_gen4, Country_us_gen5, Country_us_gen6 and Country_us_gen7. Use the generalized boundaries when creating study areas.
